      <title>What is the expected behavior of this extension?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/akismet/forum/general/what_is_the_expected_behavior_of_this_extension</link>
      <description>We have installed it but I am not sure it is right. What I see is an admin interface which lists all objects (specified in the settings) that are supposed to be checked for spam content. There is no indication if the object is spam or not, and objects are published and visible to the public whether or not they are spam. In other words, it seems the extension does not do anything to control spam. I would expect it to reject spammy comments and only those would be in the list under /reportspam. Is there a list of required attributes that content has to have to be properly evaluated?</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Mark Marsiglio)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/akismet/forum/general/what_is_the_expected_behavior_of_this_extension</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Aug 2012 19:27:31 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
